column3: White Orbs will become Black Orbs
You will keep your medals, items and hell progress.
column4: Du vil beholde prestasjoner, objekter og fremgangen i helvete.

column3: That's a lot of skulls you've got here!
column4: Det er en del hodeskaller du har her!

column3: *In case you're wondering : no, this one is not a real InApp.*
column4: * I tilfelle du lurer: Nei, det er ikke en ekte InApp.*

column3: Wow, you really want to pay $750,000 and your soul for those diamonds?
column4: Wow, ønsker du virkelig å betale $750,000 og sjela di for disse diamantene?

column3: Ah ok, phew! I thought so!
column4: Ah ok, phew! Det jeg trodde!

column3: I mean, that's a ludicrous amount of money to pay for a virtual item, you still wanna buy that?
column4: Jeg mener, det er en latterlig sum penger å betale for et virtuelt element, du ønsker fortsatt å kjøpe det?

column3: You'll probably need to get another job, a loan, sell all of your belongings... Are you sure?
column4: Du vil sannsynligvis trenge å få en jobb til, ta et lån, selge alle dine eiendeler... er du sikker?

column3: That's kind of excessive don't you think? Don't you want to cancel now?
column4: Det er litt overdrevent tror du ikke? Du vil ikke avbryte nå?

column3: Okay I guess. I mean it's cool for us, that's a lot of money, but I just want to be sure you're ok with this.
column4: Vell ok. Det er greit for oss, det er mye penger, men jeg vil bare være sikker på at du syns det er ok.

column3: Oh okay... sorry. No need to be rude.
column4: Oh Ok... beklager. Du trenger ikke å være uhøflig.

column3: I have to say, you are determined to get that pack.
column4: Jeg må si, du er bestemt på å få de diamantene.

column3: Heh, determination, that reminds me of Undertale.
column4: Hehe, besluttsomhet, det minner meg om Undertale.

column3: Have you played that game? It's super cool, you should try it.
column4: Har du spilt dette spillet? Det er ganske kult, du bør prøve det.

column3: ...and it's not even our game.  I mean Toby Fox is the guy who made it.  He's brilliant.
column4: ... og det ikke er engang vårt spill.  Jeg mener Toby Fox er fyren som lagde det.  Han er genial.

column3: I think he got inspired by Mother 3...  or is it Earthbound?
column4: Jeg tror han hentet inspirasjon fra Mother 3...  eller er det Earthbound?

column3: Hang on, is Earthbound and Mother 3 the same game? I never knew, I'm kinda confused by that.
column4: Vent litt, er Earthbound og Mother 3 det samme spille? Jeg er alltid usikker, blir litt forvirret av sånn.

column3: I think it's a lost in translation thing, kinda like Final Fantasy 6.... or 3. Whatever.
column4: Jeg tror det er en sånn "tapt i oversettelse" ting, litt som Final Fantasy 6... eller 3. Uansett.

column3: Yeah I know! It's lame right?
column4: ja, jeg vet det! Det er lame, men.

column3: The thing is, I played it once when I was a kid, but I couldn't read English.
column4: Saken er, jeg spilte det en gang når jeg var liten, men jeg kunne ikke lese Engelsk.

column3: So you know, it was kinda hard to play an RPG when you couldn't understand anything on the screen.
column4: Så du vet, det var ganske vanskelig å spille et ROLLESPILL når du ikke forstår noe på skjermen.

column3: I became good at English though!
column4: Jeg ble god i Engelsk da!

column3: My mom was like 'Video games are useless!'
column4: Min mor var sånn "videospill er ubrukelig!"

column3: But I showed her my English grades at school and she gave me a break.
column4: Men jeg viste henne mine engelsk karakterer på skolen, og hun ga meg en pause.

column3: I'm not afraid to say it, you know. I think it's cool to show her some love sometimes.
column4: Jeg ikke er redd for å si det, vet du. Jeg tror det er kult å vise henne litt kjærlighet noen ganger.

column3: You know, she makes sure you don't miss anything in your life. Food... a house, toys.
column4: Du vet, hun gjør at du ikke går glipp av noe i livet ditt. Mat... et hus, leker.

column3: And we rarely get the chance to tell her that she is awesome.
column4: Og vi får sjelden sjansen til å fortelle henne at hun er BEST.

column3: You know what? That little chat kinda made me feel better.
column4: Vet du hva? Denne praten fikk meg til, å føle meg mye bedre.

column3: It feels like you care about me.
column4: Det føles ut som du bryr deg om meg.

column3: Not only about those zombies, but about the developer behind it as well.
column4: Ikke bare om de zombiene, men også om utvikleren bak det.

column3: That's a very cool feeling, thank you. :)
column4: Det er en god følelse, takk. :)

column3: As a token of gratitude, I'll give you 5 diamonds. Do you want them?
column4: Som et tegn på takknemlighet, skal jeg gi deg 5 diamanter. Vil du ha dem?

column3: There! Thanks again for that little chat!

column4: Jeg er glad du er her igjen!

column3: I have no diamonds left for you though.
column4: Jeg har ingen diamanter igjen, for deg.

column3: Well, that's not very true... I'm the dev, so I could give you infinite diamonds if I want.
column4: Vel, det ikke er sant... Jeg som utvikler, så jeg kan gi deg uendelige diamanter hvis jeg ønsker.

column3: But that wouldnt't be fair for the other players.
column4: Men det er ikke rettferdig for de andre spillerne.

column3: Now I feel bad, because I just told you that I could, but I won't.
column4: Fikk litt dårlig samvittighet, fordi jeg fortalte deg at jeg kunne, men jeg ikke vil.

column3: What kind of friend am I?
It's kind of like if you tell your wife, 'Hey I could give you chocolate, but I won't'.
column4: Det blir det samme om du sier til din kone, 'Hei jeg kan gi deg sjokolade, men jeg vil ikke'.

column3: I should buy chocolates for my wife...
column4: Nå må jeg nesten kjøpe sjokolade til min kone...

column3: Oh well,\nThis one is on the house.
